OL,7,FIt added that he was perceived by
OL,8,Fcorporation staff as being
OL,9,F"sympathetic to, or actively part of,
OL,10,Fa campaign to undermine the BBC and
OL,11,Finfluence its political impartiality".
OL,13,FEarlier this month, Liberal Democrat
OL,14,Fleader Sir Ed Davey also called on Sir
OL,15,FKeir Starmer to sack Sir Robbie,
OL,16,Fbranding him a "Conservative crony" in
OL,17,FCommons, but the Prime Minister
OL,18,Fdeclined to comment on the "the
OL,19,Findividual runnings of the BBC".
